The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Lawyers boycott chief justice
                                                                                                                     4                                                                                      Lawyers boycott chief justice
          OUR LEGAL REPORTER                              
	Calcutta, March 23: About 6,000 Calcutta High Court lawyers today decided to boycott Chief Justice M.S. Shahs courtroom indefinitely after the high court administration refused to lend the room for an advocates condolence meeting from 3.30pm.        
	Members of the three high court lawyers associations  Bar Association, Bar Library Club and Incorporate Law Society  had decided to hold the meeting at the Chief Justices courtroom from 3.30pm. But Shah said it could only be held from four.         
	The lawyers feel the court administration was trying to curb their rights, said Sukhendu Sekhar Roy of the Bar Association. The condolence meeting was not held today.        
	SDO apology        
	Alipore SDO Mukesh Singh today apologised in the high court, which had sought action against him for not taking steps against the Calcutta Blind School teacher-in-charge who had been found guilty of misappropriating funds. Singh also said he had suspended the teacher.                                                                                                                                                            
